reviews.text: A pretty bloody good station if you ask me. Platforms are at a good height and there's a nice bridge to stare at if you're bored.

Small station with wind rain cover on both platforms. Unlike most other lines it doesn’t go into zone 1 so is less busy (more chance of getting a seat) and serves more residential areas which have poor tune connections. However, both Ticket machines regularly break when found anything other than top up an Oyster card and there is little the station guard can do because there is no ticket office. Also most annoyingly drivers sometimes depart early by 1-2 mins often to the dismay of those using the slow ticket machines. Often if the train arrives early it will leave within a minute which causes this issue.

Standard rail station with shelters away from the elements fairly well maintained. 2 Platforms, both accessible from street by steps. Platform 1 to Gospel Oak, Platform 2 Barking. Tap in & Tap out, ticket purchase machines too. Shops and pubs nearby too.
A very bland and average station which at least is lucky enough to get 4 trains an hour stopping here and have a ticket machine. No step free access is available here at all.
